<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-826-145  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 826 145.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Iandamp;CS (Instrumentation andamp; Control Systems)  Dec 1990 v63 n12 p51(5).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>High hopes for fiber optic LANs: FDDI makes its bid for control.andO;(Fiber Distributed Data Interface Network)(includes relatedarticles on the basics of fiber optics and on fiber optics-basednetworks) (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Himes, Jack.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Fiber Distributed Data Interface (FDDI) is the best choice networkstandard for new automation applications in order to ensurereliability of performance, availability and system consistency.andO;FDDI may not be the best choice for premises equipment that isalready installed, when adapters, extenders and multiplexers aremore straightforward and cost effective.andP;  FDDI is the developmentof the American National Standards Institute (ANSI) AccreditedStandardization Committee X3T9.5, for computer-to-computer and forcomputer-to-peripheral communications.andP;  The basis of the FDDIprotocol is the IEEE 802.5 standard 4Mbit/s token ring protocolformulated in 1982.andP;  FDDI offers speed and distance advantagesover copper media; FDDI networks operate at speeds of 100Mbit/sover distances of up to 2 kilometers between nodes.andP;  Up to 1,000stations can be supported, up to 100 kilometers in total networkcircumference.andP;  Both backbone and front-end applications can beused with FDDI networks.andP;  FDDI is the first US standard for fiberoptic networking and is accepted internationally.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Fiber Distributed Data Interface StandardFiber OpticsNetwork ArchitectureSpecificationsStandardsAmerican National Standards Institute.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotographchart.andO;Caption:   Front-end networks usually consist of star-like subnetworks.andO;(chart)The FDDI network consists of a backbone of dual, counter rotatingrings. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>